Title: Hope and Service
Description: Covenant Initiation Quest: Florina has requested you aid Feldan save what you can at Olcott Farm and then meet her at the Church in Everfall.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It's painful to admit, but when the Olcott farm fell to the Lost, I offered to help them reclaim their valuables. \n\nI came here with the old man, Felden Olcott, but the Withered are too many. I had no choice but to run.
InProgressResponse: Please, convince old man Olcott to leave.  If I don't get him back to town safely... well, I couldn't bear it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So you made it out of the farm with your soul intact? And I suppose you reclaimed the Olcotts' keepsakes as well? \n\nI am ashamed - you kept faith and came through, where I failed. Perhaps I am not Covenant material.

Title: The Covenant Enclave
Description: Covenant Initiation Quest: Florina has asked you to visit her brother Lethold at the Covenant enclave in south-eastern Everfall. She has attuned your spirit with the shrine, so you may travel there safely.
PlayerPrompt: "I can do that. What's the message?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Thank you. Lethold undoubtedly worries for my welfare, so please reassure him. \n\nI committed to helping people here in Oxboro for my Covenant initiation, and there's more to be done. Hopefully, I'll see you both at the enclave soon.
InProgressResponse: I really do suggest you inquire about becoming a Covenant Initiate yourself.  On Aeternum, it's critical one finds a higher purpose to serve.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Please, good visitor, tell me, have you come from Oxboro? \n\nMy dear sister Florina embarked on a quest there some time ago, and I am anxious to hear word of her welfare.

Title: Justice and Courage
Description: Covenant Initiation Quest: Lethold beseeches you to rush to Clearview Crypt to end whatever terrible acts are transpiring, save Templar Damiano, and return to him at the Covenant Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Their cowardice has very likely led them to a dark fate, though it is neither surprising nor unjust. \n\nIt appears that in their mad flight, they sought refuge in Clearview Crypt, which has now become disturbingly quiet.
InProgressResponse: I must consult with Lumen Morellus about this alleged heresy.  I hope you find Damiano, and the Initiates as well. I pray they are still whole.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The fortitude of Templar Damiano is proven by his safe return, though it is your courage that saved him. \n\nIt sounds like justice was served with the Initiates. But I wonder, how did they succumb to become Corrupted?

Title: The Lumen's Words
Description: Covenant Initiation Quest: Adjudicator Lethold has asked you to speak with Lumen Morellus at the Covenant Enclave for your final initiation test.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Very well. I must attend to cleansing the foul presence of those Initiates from our sacred halls.  When Florina returns, I hope all this is far behind us.
InProgressResponse: I suggest you speak with the Lumen soon.  There is no reason to delay.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank you for giving me this chance to express my gratitude for the rescue of Templar Damiano. \n\nI see in your eyes the light of a great potential. You would shine as a member of our order, and bring inspiration to many struggling souls.

Title: Inspiration and Redemption
Description: Covenant Initiation Quest: Morellus has enlisted you to lure the Corrupted Templar back to Nettlerest Graveyard, best him in battle, collect his cursed necklace, and return to the Convenant Enclave.
PlayerPrompt: "I can be trusted in such things."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I expected as much. The problem I need help with is related to Templar Titus Invectus, the one who oversaw the training of our fallen Initiates. \n\nI'm afraid this has driven Titus quite mad, and he, too, is now Corrupted, but through no fault of his own.
InProgressResponse: I strongly suggest you do not attempt to use the relic.  It is an insidious poison, Corruption.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: There, now we can safely say this whole sordid affair is concluded with some measure of redemption. \n\nLethold is a champion of righteousness and justice, and a strong leader.

Title: Committing to the Cause
Description: Covenant Recruitment: You can now join the Covenant.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I am thrilled to hear you affirm your interest. The Covenant will shine brighter with you standing in our ranks. \n\nGo and speak to Lumen Beyza. I have already vouched for your worthiness. And hope be with you… always.
InProgressResponse: Take your time, this is not a decision to be made lightly.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: N/A

Title: A First Step of Many
Description: Marauder Initiation Quest: Lieutenant Tibbs wants you to collect Lost Ears and a Knight's Signet ring at Lugdunum Fields for some sort of magic and then meet him at the ruin steps to the North of the farm.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That’s the spirit! Northwest's a fort filled with unbelievable wonders. Need odd things to get inside. Magic, you see. Ears from the soulless Lost, a ring from a knight. \n\nGrab that lot from Lugdunum Fields, and meet me there.
InProgressResponse: Oi! Won’t get far loitering around here with these louts! Look, you get them ears, and I promise, I’ll show you something special, sure as my name's Tibbs. \n\nYou know what they all say! Always trust a Tibbs!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Don’t give me that look, this place is FULL of wonders! Look at me, looking at you, eh! \n\nThe Marauders are my kind of soldiers, see. Family now. And I think you should join our crew. Now, how about another tip from Tibbs?

Title: Fortune Favors
Description: Marauder Initiation Quest: Lieutenant Tibbs has directed you to thrash some pirates and steal some black powder barrels, then return to the Marauders Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oi, no, no! Though it is Lost again. Pirates round here, always a pain in our side. \n\nTracked some of them down yesterday. Northeast, hiding like rats. Fight ’em, plunder ’em, burn their claim, and take their boom.
InProgressResponse: Those powder barrels, aye? We’ll be using those to impress Strou'dahia in the next step of our little plan. \n\nThe rest of the ruckus should let them know we mean business. Crash into that cave and plunder away!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh ho! Someone's got a mess of booty! Hope you gave those blackguards a good walloping.  How’s the prize? Ten percent for me then, eh? Fee, tax, and all.

Title: Threshold Guardian
Description: Marauder Initiation Quest: Lieutenant Tibbs has asked you to speak with Gladiator Strou'dahia at the Marauder Enclave for your final initiation test.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh ho! There it is! Those bombs ain't the only things with spark!  Now, go talk to Gladiator Strou'dahia, and show the Marauders what you've got!
InProgressResponse: Off you trot, mate. Talk to the Doctore and I'll await your return.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Good, stand before me. You have fought boldly so far. Should you wish to join our ranks I have one final test of strength and skill.  It is time. Let us begin.

Title: Broken Bones and Blasted Bulwarks
Description: Marauder Initiation Quest: Gladiator Stroudahia has ordered you to best Varangians and rescue captives at Stonereach Keep. You must also complete Tibb's secret mission, before returning to the Marauders' Enclave
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Varangians have begun to take some of our members prisoner. No Marauder lets their brethren stay in chains. \n\nFree the imprisoned recruits who were less fortunate, and take the Varangian Knights down a peg. Make them feel our wrath!
InProgressResponse: Were it you in captivity, you would hope for a quicker rescue? Suffering festers through inaction. \n\nMove with purpose, and guide your steel relentlessly towards your goals.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Those who would risk themselves to save their comrades are always welcome in the Marauders. \n\nWe always stand together, always look after our own. Now, I know I can trust you in battle.

Title: One of Us
Description: Marauders Recruitment Quest: You can now join the Marauders.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: This is good to hear. I would be honored to fight beside you in the battles ahead.  I've already spoken with Smiggs. Go to him and he will enter you into our charters.
InProgressResponse: Go to Smiggs with haste. Tonight, we feast!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: n/a

Title: Fickle Fusions, Fanged Folly
Description: Syndicate Initiation Quest: Aventus has hired you to lure the altered wolves to Midnight Den and destroy them, then meet him at the Syndicate Enclave to the north-east when you are finished.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, and the most valuable kind, indeed, if you assist! \n\nYou see, I've been testing alchemical lures on the local wolves. Results were promising, until one of the wolves consumed the bait... and grew in both size and ferocity.
InProgressResponse: Do not feel too sorry for the wolves.  Given the nature of the island, they are a menace in their best state.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: After that mishap with the wolves, I must return to experimenting and trying anew. A different formula, or perhaps a new approach. \n\nFortunately, research is what this place was built for. What I am built for.

Title: Over the Cliffs, and Through the Woods
Description: Syndicate Initiation Quest: Aventus has tasked you to climb the cliffs nearby into Brightwood and east into the grove of the Azoth Tree to collect water from the moat, and then return to him.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You're sharp! No progress comes without danger.  Take this bottle, mind the cliffs, follow the path into Brightwood. Go through the grove, and then to the moat.
InProgressResponse: Climb over the cliffs to the northeast. We have left markers as guides for the initiates. \n\nIf you attract unwanted attention, I recommend you hide or run. Sometimes the quickest route is draped in shadows.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Now you've seen the Azoth Tree. It was truly beautiful, no? Well worth a little danger. \n\nWelcome to Aeternum, my friend. You will have infinite time to take it in.

Title: Woes of the Wise
Description: Syndicate Initiation Quest: Aventus has asked you to speak with Cabalist Cleo Elsayad at the Syndicate Enclave for your final initiation test.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh, I believe you are. Go to her, and keep an open mind.  The task she has prepared may challenge you in more ways than one.
InProgressResponse: Go, and speak to Cleo. I eagerly await your return to the enclave.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, a moment if you please. Thank you for speaking with me, Aventus has had much to say about you. \n\nOur order eagerly accepts capable candidates, and I hoped you would perform one final test to join our ranks. Shall we?

Title: Burden of Responsibility
Description: Syndicate Initiation Quest: Cleo has requested that you travel to Broken Hull Hold, pour the sleeping draught into their wells, disrupt their reserves, and return to her at the Syndicate Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Indeed. This is an Azoth-infused sleeping draught, with which I hope to subdue our immortal foes. \n\nPour it into the wells at Broken Hull Hold, and destroy their reserves to force them to drink it.
InProgressResponse: It is a grim proposition, to be sure. But what should be done? \n\nGiven the horrific ways in which I have seen this problem approached, eternal slumber would be a blessing. We must all make difficult choices for the greater good.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You return victorious. You are truly committed to the application of knowledge, and not just its pursuit. \n\nDespite how you may feel about the act itself, do know that this work will help the people of Everfall.

Title: True Knowledge
Description: Syndicate Recruitment Quest: You can now join the Syndicate.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Now that is some joyous news. Your letters of recommendation have already been furnished.  Go to Scrivener Astrid and she will process your records into our charters.
InProgressResponse: Please, go to Astrid. She already has your letters of recommendation in her files.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: N/A

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator quest from the Enclave.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I knew I saw that spark of ambition. You are Marauder through and through, Soldier.\n\nYou seek to become a Gladiator then? Complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Gladiator in Cutlass Keys.
InProgressResponse: Now that you have officially joined our ranks, we expect you to seize every opportunity to gain honor.\n\nMissions are available anytime on the Faction Board here, and in other settlements.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Enclave.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I knew I saw that spark of ambition. You are Marauder through and through, Soldier.\n\nYou seek to become a Gladiator then? Complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Gladiator in Cutlass Keys.
InProgressResponse: We are strongest together. Let us endeavor to bring victory to the Marauders.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Gladiator
Description: Defeat the Lost and their leader, Pirate Lawrence of the Long Shadow to prove you're worthy to advance to the rank of Gladiator. Talk to Commander Silas at the Marauder Enclave when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "Can't be too hard. You made it."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh, a really smart tongue on this one. It's a shame I don't have time to make you eat those words.\n\nThis challenge should be punishment enough, anyhow. It's helpful to me either way if you fail.
InProgressResponse: Smart. You should make sure you're ready before facing Lawrence. Could take some time. Possibly forever.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Saw you speaking with Tibbs over there. Not sure that was what I had assigned but I bet you were getting help.\n\nDoesn't surprise me, he's just as useless as you are. Talk to him all you like you, it won't help you.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Ravager
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Ravager and then complete the Trial of the Ravager Quest from the Faction Representative in Weaver's Fen.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Ravager
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat a clan of bears in Greyvale Grotto to advance to the rank of Ravager. Talk to Commander Silas at the Marauder Enclave when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "Unlikely, but tell me what I need to do."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ha ha! Still cocky. But the bears of Greyvale Grotto will teach you a bit about humility.\n\nHead there and do your best to avoid getting mauled by Grimclaw. In the unlikely event you survive, you'll be a Ravager.
InProgressResponse: Make your way to Greyvale Grotto in Brightwood. And try not to die. It reflects poorly on all of us when Gladiators get eaten by wild beasts.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Back so soon? I assume you've come to concede. I suppose you can still serve under Tibbs' command, if he isn't too ashamed of you.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Destroyer
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Destroyer and then complete the Trial of the Destroyer quest from the Faction Representative at the Enclave.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Destroyer
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat the corrupted ex-marauders in the Great Cleave. Talk to Lieutenant Tibbs at the Marauder Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Unfortunately, yes. We fought together, honorably, at one time, but due to events in the Great Cleave, he turned. \n\nGladiator Strou'dahia believes it might have been the influence of an amulet Florent wore.
InProgressResponse: Careful out there. Great Cleave is treacherous… for all of us. Report to Strou'dahia once you've recovered the amulet.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Welcome back. So you recovered Florent's amulet? If it was the amulet that caused the old boy to fall, any clues to where it came from?

Title: Marauder Advancement: Commander
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Commander and then complete the Trial of the Commander quest from the Faction Representative at the Enclave.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Commander
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat Corrupted Commander Silas and return the corrupted amulet to prove you're worthy to advance to the rank of Commander. Talk to Lieutenant Tibbs at the Marauder Enclave when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I am ready. What do I do?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Silas gave into her fury and pride and embraced Corruption. It is… a stain on the honor of all Marauders. I am sorry to say that Silas still wears an amulet awarded to her.
InProgressResponse: Our task is grim, but the Marauders must take the difficult path, even when dealing with those we do not like.\n\nSilas was a good Marauder for all her faults. But allowing the Corruption to overtake you is inexcusable.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It is done then? Ah yes, this amulet is a symbol of your accomplishment. You have served as an exemplar of the tenets we adhere to.\n\nLet this be a lesson to all those who strive for greatness in the Marauders.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Champion
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Champion and then complete the Trial of the Champion Quest from the Faction Representative at the Enclave.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Champion
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nBrave the dangers of Brimstone Sands and Hornhold to prove you're worthy to advance to the rank of Champion. Talk to Gladiator Strou'dahia at the Marauder Enclave when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I am always ready for a new challenge."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: As a Commander of the Marauders, you have the chance to become one of the very best of the Marauders.\n\nBut I have a new trial, a station that has not been achieved for generations. A true Champion.
InProgressResponse: Many have failed at this trial, so I do not have to tell you twice to think with a keen mind and a cautious eye.\n\nThe rest... well that is up to you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I see you have spoken with Tibb. The look on his face was all that I needed.\n\n I will take the trophies that you earned. The Maruaders will keep them as a reminder of what you have accomplished.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Enclave.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There are no shortcuts in the Syndicate; it will take time and considerable effort to advance. \n\nTo become a Scrivener, you will complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Scrivener in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: Now that you have officially joined in our enterprise, you should always seek ways to advance our interests.\n\nMissions are available anytime on the Faction Board here, and in other settlements.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Enclave.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There are no shortcuts in the Syndicate; it will take time and considerable effort to advance. \n\nTo become a Scrivener, you will complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Scrivener in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: I humbly greet you, truth seeker.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Scrivener
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat Lost Gheist Malikor and use the Psychokinetic Absorber to capture any ectoplasm to earn the rank of Scrivener. Talk to Alchemist Krockes at the Syndicate Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You have arrived at the perfect moment, for I am ready to test my new Psychokinetic Absorber.\n\nDid you know that some of the Lost still possess small traces of their souls?
InProgressResponse: Have you located Malikor yet? He's somewhere out there.\n\nUse the Absorber and bring back the traces of his soul!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, at last! Yes, yes, you see? There are traces of Malikor's soul in here! This could change everything!\n\nThis device will surely cause a revolution in our studies of the Lost!

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Chronicler
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Chronicler and then complete the Trial of the Chronicler quest from Alchemist Krockes at the Enclave.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Chronicler
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nGather ectoplasm and soul traces from the various Lost in Periville and return to Alchemist Krockes at the Syndicate Enclave to earn the rank of Chronicler.
PlayerPrompt: "Yes. Will you administer my trial again?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: After our first success? Of course! I consider you a most audacious companion! \n\nGather up specimens from Periville, and let us repeat our experiment on a new subject.
InProgressResponse: Gather the specimens for our work in the Fen, and then I will see you advanced in rank.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Really? You got all of it? And rather quickly too, I think.\n\nYour abilities once again prove you are an invaluable resource!

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Cabalist
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Cabalist and then complete the Trial of the Cabalist quest from Alchemist Krockes at the Enclave.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Cabalist
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nPlace Psychokinetic Absorbers at strategic points in Mourningdale to earn the rank of Cabalist. Talk to Alchemist Krockes at the Syndicate Enclave when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh right yes of course, I am doing perfectly well. I just was distracted.\n\nIt matters not, we have yet another prototype to test. This time, a unique one that must be tested in Mourningdale!
InProgressResponse: Those Psychokinetic Absorbers won't place themselves.\n\nThe sooner, the better. The research never ends, my friend!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Perfect! Perfect! You have accomplished quite the feat, and this harvest will be invaluable to me-- and the Syndicate of course.\n\nBut I must collect them, yes I must soon.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Alchemist
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Alchemist and then complete the Trial of the Alchemist quest from Cleo Elsayad at the Enclave.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Alchemist
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat Alchemist Krockes and absorb his soul into the Psychokinetic Absorber and then return it to Cleo Elsayad to earn the rank of Alchemist. Talk to Cleo Elsayad at the  Syndicate Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The way it always does with the undisciplined. Too enamored of their research and their reputation.\n\nKrockes was simply not strong-minded enough. You are ready to face your final trial, are you not?
InProgressResponse: When you find Krockes, don't hesitate. I suspect he has become quite… volatile.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Then the deed is done? Krockes is no more? Well done!\n\nThe integrity of our research must be preserved. You have served with distinction and earned the rank of Alchemist. Congratulations!

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Magus
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Magus and then complete the Trial of the Magus quest from Cleo Elsayad at the Enclave.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Magus
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nVenture to Tempestas Custodia to obtain the work of Syndicate Researcher Sigurdsson and return it to Cleo Elsayad to earn the rank of Magus. Talk to Cleo Elsayad at the Syndicate Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah yes, well you see there had been Syndicate researchers dispatched to study these sites. One of particular interest was called Tempestas Custodia.\n\nA researcher named Sigurdsson volunteered to delve further into the site.
InProgressResponse: Sigurdsson was a fine researcher, but I do wonder if he was in over his head in the Elysian Wilds.\n\nThe Syndicate's mission often requires us to visit such untamed lands.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well done, I knew that you could be trusted with such a monumental task. You will be named a Magus immediately.\n\nAnd so shall Sigurdsson, should he ever return. Hope springs eternal here in Aeternum, after all.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from Beatris Roose in the Covenant Enclave.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from Beatris Roose in the Covenant Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It will take great heart and great courage should you wish to rise within the order.\n\nTo become a Templar, you'll need to complete missions to earn reputation, and then face the Trial of the Templar in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: Now that you have joined in our cause, you must carry the light into the world at every chance.\n\nMissions are available anytime on the Faction Board here, and in other settlements.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from Beatris Roose in the Covenant Enclave.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from Beatris Roose in the Covenant Enclave.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It will take great heart and great courage should you wish to rise within the order.\n\nTo become a Templar, you'll need to complete missions to earn reputation, and then face the Trial of the Templar in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: The light of the Covenant shines within you.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Templar
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nTrack down the Apostate Covenant Initiate Bremen Luca and attempt to discover what happened to him to advance to the rank of Templar. Talk to Templar Roose at the Covenant Enclave when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I am ready. What do I do?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: An Initiate, like yourself, has asked some uncomfortable questions. A few that, I'm afraid, we cannot allow.\n\nHe was named an Apostate, and it seems in his despair that he's fallen Lost. We must lay him to his final rest.
InProgressResponse: Find the Apostate and offer him his final rest.\n\nMay he at last find peace, at least for some time.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, you have returned! I have taken over the Trial. Adjudicator Roose is otherwise occupied.\n\nI am Livia Luca, Covenant Adjudicator. If that name sounds familiar it is because I am the mother of Bremen Luca.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Excubitor
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Excubitor and then complete the Trial of the Excubitor quest from Livia Luca at the Covenant Enclave.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Excubitor
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nFind the second page of the journal of Bremen Luca to advance to the rank of Excubitor. Talk to Livia Luca at the Covenant Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Something of grave concern. My son was named an Apostate, yet he was not the only one excommunicated from the Covenant.\n\nI fear this runs deeper than I thought. I believe that there was a conspiracy against my son.
InProgressResponse: Travel the Fen and find what my son was investigating. Then I will grant you the rank of Excubitor.\n\nRemember, we must not tell the others.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You found this page? And… prayer beads? These are beads of the Covenant. That must mean these were once Covenant members.\n\n I'm afraid this has much darker implications than I originally thought.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Lumen
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Lumen and then complete the Trial of the Lumen quest from Livia Luca at the Covenant Enclave.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Lumen
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nFind Bremen Luca's journal at Hollowing Fort and recover Prayer Beads from Corrupted Templars to earn the rank of Lumen. Talk to Adjudicator Luca at the Covenant Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have continued piecing together the fragments of my son's journals. He mentioned someone called Templar Ambrose who went to Great Cleave.\n\nI'm don’t know him, but I need you to find out more. With him lies the answers.
InProgressResponse: Your help has been invaluable to me, and to the entire Covenant.\n\nWe will uncover the truth, and your valor will be recognized. But first, we must find the evidence.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This was when he discovered about some of the leaders, then. He uncovered the fallen of the Covenant, and they punished him for seeking the truth.\n\nIt all started with this Templar Ambrose, his fall started Bremen's path.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Adjudicator
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Adjudicator and then complete the Trial of the Adjudicator quest from the Lethold at the Covenant Enclave.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Adjudicator
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nLay Corrupted Adjudicator Luca to rest and find Adjudicator Roose to earn the rank of Adjudicator. Talk to Lethold at the Covenant Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Our scouts report that she has turned to the Corruption. If that is the case, she must be dealt with, and it may mean that Adjudicator Roose is in peril as well.\n\nThis is no mean task, but... you must track down Luca.
InProgressResponse: I am sobered by the notion that Luca might have fallen, but we must do what is necessary for the Covenant.\n\nMay justice be swift for those who turn to the Corruption.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It's done, then? Perhaps she will find peace in death.\n\nAnd I see that Adjudicator Roose has returned. You have done what has been asked of you and more.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Paladin
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Paladin and then complete the Trial of the Paladin quest from the Lethold at the Covenant Enclave.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Paladin
Description: <font color="#b2aea1">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\n Find and defeat the Covenant Traitor in the Elysian Wilds to earn the rank of Paladin. Talk to Lethold at the Covenant Enclave when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes. There are many things we do not know, but what is certain is that we have no communication with those left at Old First Light.\n\nI fear the worst has happened.
InProgressResponse: Be on your guard out in the Elysian Wilds. Much has changed out there and some truly formidable enemies now prowl the wildlands. Keep a sharp eye.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What have you found about the settlement in Old First Light?\n\nWho was this Simon Jeffrey and Rotgut?
